# Code Quality & Testability

## One Responsibility Per File

| File contains | One of |
|---------------|--------|
| `verify_plate_use_case.py` | Single use case class |
| `plate_number.py` | Single value object |
| `sighting_repository.py` | Single repository implementation |
| `verify_plate_handler.py` | Single route handler group |

Split when a file exceeds ~150 lines or handles multiple reasons to change.

## Small Functions

- Target **≤ 25 lines** per function; extract helpers when logic branches grow.
- Use cases: `execute()` orchestrates; delegate to private methods or domain services.
- No function should do I/O **and** business rule evaluation **and** response mapping.

```
# ✅ GOOD
async def execute(self, command: VerifyCommand) -> VerifyResult:
    plate = PlateNumber.normalize(command.plate_text)
    vehicle = await self._registry.find_by_plate(plate)
    return self._policy.evaluate(plate, vehicle)
```

## Naming

| Artifact | Convention |
|----------|------------|
| Use case | `{Verb}{Noun}UseCase` |
| Port | `{Noun}Port` |
| Handler | `{resource}_handler.py` |
| Test | `test_{module}.py` |

## Testability Requirements

| Layer | Test With |
|-------|-----------|
| Domain | Pure unit tests — no mocks |
| Application | Fake outbound ports |
| Infrastructure | Integration tests — test DB, fixtures |
| Interfaces | Contract tests — mock use cases |

Every new use case → `tests/unit/application/`.  
Every new domain service → `tests/unit/domain/`.

## Test Rules

- Tests must be deterministic — no real network or GPU in unit tests.
- Fixture images: `tests/fixtures/data/images/`.
- Fake ports: `tests/fixtures/fakes/`.
- Mirror `src/sentinel_anpr/` structure under `tests/`.

## PR Checklist

- [ ] Single responsibility per new file
- [ ] Functions small and named by intent
- [ ] Unit tests for domain/application changes
- [ ] No domain imports from outer layers
- [ ] Ports defined before adapter implementations
